<s1 title="MX4J remote administration">

<p>MX4J can be used to remotely administer a Resin server.</p>
<p>(contributed by D Dunkley)</p>

<p>
</p><ol>
<li>Install the MX4J libraries in <code>$RESIN_HOME/lib/mx4j/*</code>
</li><li>start Resin with <br/><code>bin/httpd -Djavax.management.builder.initial=mx4j.server.MX4JMBeanServerBuilder</code>
</li></ol>

<p>MBeans can be managed with MX4J's GUI console.</p>

<p>See also:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/mx4j/">MX4J project home page</a>
</li></ul>


</s1>
